        <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:800;margin-bottom:1rem;color:#0c4a6e;">About WASA Lahore</h2>
        <p>Water and Sanitation Agency (WASA) Lahore is the government authority responsible for water supply and sewerage management for <strong>Lahore city</strong> — Pakistan's second-largest metropolis with a population of 14+ million. WASA Lahore operates under the Lahore Development Authority (LDA) and the Punjab government, supplying treated drinking water to all residential, commercial, and industrial consumers within Lahore district.</p>
        <p>WASA Lahore manages water extraction from deep tube wells across Lahore, water treatment plants, and a citywide distribution network of pipes, storage reservoirs, and pumping stations. The agency is also responsible for sewerage collection and treatment — preventing untreated sewage from entering Lahore's water table and the Ravi River.</p>
        <p>WASA Lahore's billing system has modernized significantly in recent years. Key digital features include: <strong>QR code payment</strong> printed on bills, <strong>WhatsApp bill service</strong> (0334-1334470), <strong>1-Link ATM payments</strong> (biller code 100059), and the <strong>Punjab WASA online portal</strong> (wasa.punjab.gov.pk). Monthly water bills cover both water consumption and sewerage charges.</p>
